snippet.textDisplay:
GB was lucky this year.

1. Facing KC without Mahomes.

2. Facing Min the second time with no dalvin cook.

3. Both games against Detroit were close to losses and phantom penalties helped them win. Especially that second Det game.

4. Because of that + easy schedule, they slid into the 2 seed. They got to host Seattle on rest, Seattle lives and dies by Wilson so they werent a legit SB contender in anyone's mind. And GB still let them come back and have the ball with a chance to win.

The Packers have talent and they were definitely worthy of being in the playoffs but the reality is that they had a lot of things fall into place for them this year that helped get them to that 13 and 3 record. I feel 9-7 or 10-6 was more what they looked like.

So Green Bay isn't good because they..... won games they should have? He's acting like he's the only one who predicted SF winning.

Don't get me wrong either....SF was the better team and i fully expected the end result. But knocking GB because you expected it to be New Orleans instead is kind of ridiculous.

New Orleans chokes at home to a team GB had just ran thru a couple weeks earlier on the road. Then GB beats a Seattle team that was less than a yard away from putting SF on the road the entire playoffs.

NFL is still winner take all. Not best out of 3. It's also not college. You can't pick your schedule. You earn what you get.

First year head coach and new staff. A ton of roster turnover. 13-3. A bye week. A home playoff win and spot in NFCC. Not that bad if you ask me.

Oh and brw...Colin also predicted the Steelers going 11-5, Eagles 11-5, SF winning 9 games, Rams winning their division, Browns winning 9 games, SD 10 wins, Ravens, Vikings and Saints each with 8 wins, Jets and Bears 9 wins, Bills 7 wins and the Falcons winning the NFC South...... before the season started. Green Bay coasted to a 13-3 through a winning turnover differential against a strangely weak schedule for an NFL team. They finished with a negative yardage differential on the season, ranking 18th in both yards for and against.


Their defense, will quite good at forcing interceptions, was 18th in yards given up per pass and 24th in yards given up per rush.


Also, their point differential ranked 10th in the league, and that point differential indicated that this team performed around the level of a 10-6 team.


Where are these stats that show how great Green Bay was again?
